snippet.textDisplay: Right now in a shaky Puerto Rico, you feel like if you are traveling through the ocean in a small boat. The 6.4 shake in my hometown of Cabo Rojo, PR was strongly felt but the damages were minor and reported mostly from hotels and houses supported by columns. The serious damages occurred in the cities of Guanica, Guayanilla, Ponce and nearby areas that are expecting to confront months of reconstruction while the government of Puerto Rico find a way to relieve the never-ending economic crisis.
